    dc:creator "Giri, Varad B.; Bauer, Aaron M.; Mohapatra, Pratyush P.; Srinivasulu, Chelmala; Agarwal, Ishan" ;
    dc:date "2017" ;
    dc:title "A new species of large-bodied, tuberculate Hemidactylus Oken (Squamata: Gekkonidae) from the Eastern Ghats, India" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1045735>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1045737>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1045739>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1045741>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1045743>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1045745>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1045747>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1045749> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1045735>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Dorsal view of Hemidactylus sushilduttai sp. nov. holotype, NCBS-AU 157: Photo by Varad Giri & Akshay Khandekar. Scale bar = 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1045735/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1045737>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Head of Hemidactylus sushilduttai sp. nov. holotype, NCBS-AU 157: A) dorsal view, B) lateral view, C) ventral view. Photos by Varad Giri & Akshay Khandekar. Scale bar = 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1045737/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1045739>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Details of dorsal pholidosis of Hemidactylus sushilduttai sp. nov. holotype, NCBS-AU 157, showing irregularly arranged longitudinal rows of enlarged, trihedral tubercles at midbody. Photo by Varad Giri & Akshay Khandekar. Scale bar = 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1045739/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1045741>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Precloacal region of Hemidactylus sushilduttai sp. nov. holotype, NCBS-AU 157 showing series of 11 femoral pores on left and right side separated medially by eight pore-less scales. Photo by Varad Giri & Akshay Khandekar. Scale bar = 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1045741/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1045743>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. A) ventral view of right manus and B) ventral view of right pes of Hemidactylus sushilduttai sp. nov. holotype (NCBS-AU 157). Photo by Varad Giri & Akshay Khandekar. Scale bar = 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1045743/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1045745>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Tail of Hemidactylus sushilduttai sp. nov. holotype, NCBS-AU 157: A) dorsal view, B) ventral view. Photo by Varad Giri & Akshay Khandekar. Scale bar = 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1045745/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1045747>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Hemidactylus sushilduttai sp. nov. in life, A) holotype NCBS-AU 157, B) paratype ESV 109. Photos by Ishan Agarwal." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1045747/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1045749>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Relief map of India and Sri Lanka showing type localities of members of the prashadi clade (Bansal & Karanth 2010) that exceed 90 mm SVL (stars) and the known distribution of Hemidactylus sushilduttai sp. nov. (circles). The imprecise type locality of Hemidactylus acanthopholis (Tirunelveli District) is plotted as the city of Tirunelveli in the map, although this species probably occurs only in the adjacent hills west of the city, with the nearest likely habitat approximately 30 km to the west (Mirza & Sanap 2014)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1045749/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

